<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:fb="http://www.facebook.com/2008/fbml">
<body>

<p>DanceDeets requires a facebook account to use it. The site relies heavily on facebook events, and the facebook terms of service prevent us from showing that information to you without your login information. Log in below to gain access to DanceDeets.

<p><fb:login-button onlogin="window.location=getNextUrl();" perms="user_location,rsvp_event,offline_access,email,user_events"></fb:login-button>

<p>DanceDeets will request some permissions from you, here is a list of the permissions and the reasons why they are necessary:
<ul>
<li><b>Access my public information</b>: show you which of your friends are attending dance events.
<li><b>Send me email</b>: emails you about upcoming dance events that meet your criteria and interest.
<li><b>Access my data any time</b>: lets you get weekly emails with upcoming event info, even if you haven't been to www.dancedeets.com recently.
<li><b>Manage my events</b>: lets you click "Attending" and add facebook events directly from DanceDeets.
<li><b>Access my profile information (Events)</b>: shows you what events you are attending (or not attending).
<li><b>Access my contact information (Current Location)</b>: only shows you dance events in your area.
</ul>

<div id="fb-root"></div>
<script src="http://connect.facebook.net/en_US/all.js"></script>
<script>
  function getNextUrl() {
    return '$next';
  }

  FB.init({appId: '$api_key', status: true,
         cookie: true, xfbml: true});
</script>
</body>
</html>
